You shouldn't have to specify that you want it the way the menu advertises it, that should be the default. I know it isn't supposed to be that way, but that was the excuse they gave us when they messed it up and had to redeliver our food. It is a step above Subway The menu board is wayyyy tooo busy.. Sandwich was ok. but if you want more for your money, you need to  drive maybe 3 minutes away and go to Englund II Deli. A local place. They have big subs..  Jimmys has a sub that called a Gargantua not sure of its size but it is $7.49 plus extras. (Englund II has a  sub that's 18 inches with the works. $10.49 enough for 4 people or one person to eat over 3 days. I know.)  Just so you know I have no association with Englund Deli. I am a foodie who likes the biggest bang for my money.
